{
  "texts": [
    "Several recent methods attempt to improve tactical coaching and player decision-making through artificial intelligence (AI) tools, using a wide variety of data types from videos to tracking sensors and applying diverse algorithms ranging from simple logistic regression to elaborate neural network architectures.",
    "Such methods have been employed to help predict shot events from videos 3, forecast off-screen movement from spatio-temporal data 4, determine whether a match is inplay or interrupted 5, or identify player actions 6.",
    "The execution of agreed-upon plans by players on the pitch is highly dynamic and imperfect, depending on numerous factors including player fitness and fatigue, variations in player movement and positioning, weather, the state of the pitch, and the reaction of the opposing team.",
    "In contrast, set pieces provide an opportunity to exert more control on the outcome, as the brief interruption in play allows the players to reposition according to one of the practiced and preagreed patterns, and make a deliberate attempt towards the goal.",
    "Examples of such set pieces include free kicks, corner kicks, goal kicks, throw-ins, and penalties 2."
  ]
}